    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="1018"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1018">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 (Potsdam)/7–3045</note>
                <head>No. 1018<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Proposal by the British Delegation</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1018fn1">Attachment 13 to the summary of the Tenth Meeting
                        of the Foreign Ministers, July 30. See <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_495">pp. 495</ref>, <ref target="#pg_498">498</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <gloss target="#t_War1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">War</hi>
                    </gloss>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Crimes</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum by the British Delegation Dated</hi> 13<hi
                        rend="smallcaps">th</hi> [<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>] <hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >July</hi>, 1945</p>
                <p>The British Delegation placed this matter on the Agenda of the Conference.<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d1018fn2">See <ref target="frus1945Berlinv01#d176">vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, document No. 176</ref>.</note> They
                    consider it most desirable, in view of the great public interest throughout the
                    world in the major <gloss target="#t_War1">war</gloss> criminals being brought
                    to just and speedy punishment, that an agreement should be reached between the
                    Three Governments to insert a paragraph on the lines suggested below in the
                    Protocol and Communiqué.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“The Three Governments have taken note of the discussions which have been
                        proceeding in recent weeks in London<note n="3" xml:id="d1018fn3">For the
                            London discussions referred to, for the text of the Agreement of August
                            8, 1945, signed at the conclusion of those discussions, and for the text
                            of the Charter of the International Military Tribunal annexed to that
                            Agreement, see <hi rend="italic">Report of <persName corresp="#p_JRH1"
                                    >Robert H. Jackson</persName>, United States Representative to
                                the International Conference on Military Trials, London,
                            1945</hi>.</note> between British, United States, Soviet and French
                        representatives with a view to reaching agreement on the methods of trial of
                        those major <gloss target="#t_War1">war</gloss> criminals whose crimes under
                        the Moscow Declaration of October, 1943 have no particular geographical
                        localisation. The Three Governments reaffirm their intention to bring these
                        criminals to swift and sure justice. They hope that the negotiations in
                        London will result in speedy agreement being reached for this purpose, and
                        they regard it as a matter of great importance that the trial of these major
                        criminals should begin at the earliest possible date.”<note n="4"
                            xml:id="d1018fn4">One copy of this paper bears the following manuscript
                            notation: “Agreed”.</note>
                    </p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Potsdam</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-30">30th July,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
